                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="78032" author="pjones" created="Thu, 27 Feb 2014 17:27:26 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ok - thanks Gabriele!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="78027" author="gabriele.paciucci" created="Thu, 27 Feb 2014 17:23:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I have talked with the customer, please mark this issue as resolved. Thanks&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="76323" author="cliffw" created="Wed, 5 Feb 2014 23:43:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There should be no issues during a downgrade, as you are moving only two minor releases. There are no changes to the Lustre configuration, only versions of the RPMs change. For downgrade, you would simply re-install the previous set of RPMS. Also, there are no issues in this case with a mixed environment, so you can do a rolling upgrade or a rolling downgrade. The cluster and clients should work just fine with any mix of 1.8.7-wc1 and 1.8.9-wc1. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="76254" author="lustre.support" created="Wed, 5 Feb 2014 09:37:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, &lt;br/&gt;
we must upgrade Lustre in production environment from 1.8.7wc1 to 1.8.9wc1, but the customer asks for a rollback plain if something not works. Is there an official procedure to downgrade ? &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;regards&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="76177" author="pjones" created="Tue, 4 Feb 2014 14:44:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This should work ok in theory but we only explicitly tested upgrading/downgrading from/to 1.8.8-wc1 during 1.8.9-wc1 release testing. We would certainly help you with any problems that you ran into during such a downgrade. Having said that, why would you want to do such a downgrade? Have you run into issues on 1.8.9-wc1?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="76169" author="lustre.support" created="Tue, 4 Feb 2014 09:02:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi, the cluster is initially 1.8.7-wc1 and the upgraded to 1.8.9&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;regards&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="75927" author="pjones" created="Thu, 30 Jan 2014 14:35:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Could you please clarify - was this cluster initially installed as 1.8.7-wc1 then upgraded to 1.8.9-wc1, or was it a fresh install of 1.8.9-wc1?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
